			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Lad Tobin</span></strong> lives in Kittery Point, Maine, and commutes to his teaching job at Boston College. He has spent the past decade crafting painfully personal essays about his teens. He figures that at this rate he won&rsquo;t be writing about what is happening to him now until he is in his nineties.</p><a href="/contributors/lad-tobin" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
